ator','configcalculator',NULL,'Zero_Main','Shop_ConfigCalculator_Grid','yes','yes','yes','no',10,'Конфигурации калькулятора','Конфигурации калькулятора',NULL,'Конфигурации калькулятора','Конфигурации калькулятора','Конфигурации калькулятора',NULL,NULL),(79,78,'/admin/shop/configcalculator/edit','edit',NULL,'Zero_Main','Shop_ConfigCalculator_Edit','yes','yes','no','no',10,'Изменение','Изменение',NULL,'Изменение','Изменение','Изменение',NULL,NULL),(80,1,'/web','web','/web/hosting',NULL,NULL,'no','yes','yes','yes',10,'WEB','WEB',NULL,'Web','Web','Web',NULL,NULL),(81,1,'/solutions','solutions',NULL,'Content_Page','Content_Section_Page','no','yes','yes','yes',40,'SOLUTIONS','SOLUTIONS',NULL,'SOLUTIONS','SOLUTIONS','SOLUTIONS','<p>We won&rsquo;t accept your claim/complaint about violation of copyright and associated rights unless made in writing and delivered to us by registered mail.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our postal address: 19/2, Lva Tolstogo st., 119021, Moscow, Attn: Mir Telematiki Ltd.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The claim/complaint should include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Applicant name (first names and surname &mdash; for individuals, full trade name &mdash; for companies);</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Registered address &mdash; for companies, registered address and/or place of residence &mdash; for individuals (apartment /suite, street, city, region, republic/country and zip code), i.e. the address to which a reply to your claim/complaint should be sent to; and your e-mail address;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>State registration certificate data &mdash; for companies; identity document (passport or its equivalent) data &mdash; for individuals;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your claim/complaint should specify the grounds for its filing and all material facts. If any materials/documents/information etc. are available on any websites and that violates any copyright, your claim/complaint should necessarily indicate full references to specific page (pages) of the website on which the given information and materials are located.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also the claim should state that the applicant undertakes to indemnify for losses incurred by the Operator in case of unauthorized website ban, if afterwards the claim is proved to contain false information about violation of the applicant&#39;s copyright.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The claim should be accompanied by certified copies of documents proving the applicant&#39;s copyright.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All pages of such enclosed copies should be signed and stamped by the applicant company chief executive; or such enclosed copies should be certified by a notary public if the applicant is an individual. The claim/complaint made for and on behalf of a company should be signed and stamped by its chief executive or by any authorized representative acting under the power-of-attorney, the copy of which to be enclosed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The claim made for and on behalf of an individual applicant should be signed by the applicant itself; and the signature on the claim should be certified by a notary public.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All claims/complaints are being considered within 60 days. In case of claim satisfaction, infringing materials could be directly deleted with any technical means. The company will take all necessary measures and will notify the applicant about it by e-mail indicated in the claim. If a claim is not accepted for satisfaction or the remedy is not feasible, the company shall provide the applicant with the grounds for its refusal in writing by mail to the address indicated in the claim.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Any claims made by anonyms or delivered by e-mail or fax WILL NOT be accepted and considered.</p>','section/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/81/promo_text_02.png'),(82,81,'/solutions/load-balancing','load-balancing',NULL,'Content_Page','Content_Section_Page','no','yes','yes','yes',40,'Server Load balancing','Server Load balancing','Server Load balancing','Server Load balancing','Server Load balancing','Server Load balancing','<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc;\"><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><strong>Fault tolerance and scalability of project resources</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">Load Balancer allows you to distribute tasks across multiple devices connected on a logical level or physically. This service will increase the resilience of projects due to their redundancy, optimized scalability and improved fault tolerance.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">For more information, please, contact our <a href=\"mailto:sales@hostkey.com\"><span style=\"color:#945AE0;\"><b>Sales department</b></span></a></span></span></p>','section/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/82/slb.png'),(83,81,'/solutions/ddos-protection','ddos-protection',NULL,'Content_Page','Content_Section_Page','no','yes','yes','yes',20,'DDoS','DDoS',NULL,'DDoS','DDoS','DDoS','<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">DDoS attacks (Distributed-Denial-of-Service) &mdash; attacks aimed at disabling the telecommunication equipment, network congestion, equipment resource depletion of the end or data theft.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">This type of cyber-attacks has long been one of the conventional methods used by competitors as clearly demonstrated on <b><a href=\"http://www.digitalattackmap.com/#anim=1&amp;color=0&amp;country=ALL&amp;list=0&amp;time=16765&amp;view=map\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#945AE0;\">a digital attack map</span></a></b></span> &mdash; the visualization of attacks on global Internet traffic, created by ATLAS in conjunction with Google Ideas.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#FF692d;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\"><span style=\"font-size:26px\"><strong>Russia</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">DDoS protection service offered by HOSTKEY has been jointly implemented with our technology partners: network backbone operator RETN and Arbor Networks &mdash; global leader in network security solutions.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:24px\">Service features</span></strong></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">Protection against bulk Volumetric-attacks, all types of traffic are being filtered.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">Connection to the service does not require a prolonged setup, software installation, etc. The server connects to a secure network and basic filters are turned on automatically.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">The possibility of &quot;additional training&quot; of the system. Within two weeks from the connection date, the system teaches itself by analyzing traffic types. Further, there will be a possibility of adjusting filtering rules.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">Only cleaned incoming traffic is being charged.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">Extended functional monitoring system available via the Client Area that provides information on filtering and identifies bottlenecks and vulnerabilities.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:24px\">Price and conditions of the DDoS protection service</span></strong></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">Connection to the service is free of charge.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<table class=\"table_stan\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\"width: 50%;\"><strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">Volume of cleaned incoming traffic</span></span></strong></strong></th>\r\n			<th style=\"width: 50%;\"><strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">Monthly, &euro; per 1 IP</span></span></strong></strong></th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">1 Tb or less</span></span></strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">50</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">2 Tb</span></span></strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">90</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">3 Tb</span></span></strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">135</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">4 Tb</span></span></strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">165</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">5 Tb</span></span></strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">195</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">For non-standard projects we offer the possibility of charging the dedicated bandwidth of <b>100 Mbps without traffic limitations</b>. Price &mdash; &euro;252 monthly.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:24px\">To activate the service, please, contact our <a href=\"mailto:sales@hostkey.com\"><span style=\"color:#945AE0;\"><b>Sales department</b></span></a> and provide the following information</span></strong></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">Select the appropriate tariff plan; specify the number of servers that will require protection.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">Specify the IP-address of the server(s). Note: the protection is only offered for dedicated servers and colocation services, provided by HOSTKEY. If you use your own IP ranges, please, <a href=\"mailto:sales@hostkey.com\"><span style=\"color:#945AE0;\"><b>contact us</b></span></a> to identify technical possibilities and likely solutions. For example, we can announce your network through the filters. </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">DDoS protection will be activated within &hellip;.after paying the invoice.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">If you suspect a DDoS attack, please, contact our <a href=\"mailto:support@hostkey.com\"><span style=\"color:#945AE0;\"><b>technical support</b></span></a>. HOSTKEY engineers will be fine-tuning the filtration system in the real time for the most effective protection against the attack, and you will be analyzing the result.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#FF692d;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\"><span style=\"font-size:26px\"><strong>The Netherlands</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">For DDoS protection we use the resources of Serverius data center.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">Serverius provides a multi-layer DDoS protection system that protects against all modern DDoS attack methods.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">The cleaning engine is an own build multilayer scrubbing system that is using carriers, router firewalls, DDoS scrubbing hardware and specific user application defense techniques. It is not one magic scrubbing box, it&rsquo;s a combination of different layers. Carrier Flowspec techniques, edge switching OpenFlow, DDoS scrubbing hardware to specific client application settings. All performed by known hardware and software vendors that all work simultaneously. The Serverius own build &ldquo;clean conductor&rdquo; robot conducts the orchestra, it ensures that all cleaning components are dynamically working together as one.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\"><span style=\"font-size:24px\">Advantages of DDoS protection service</span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">Incoming traffic limit &mdash; 800 Gbps.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">DDoS Layer 3, 4 and 7 protection (volume and application attack protection).</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">The most advanced client panel in the world &mdash; Base Package.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">The filter can operate in in-line or out of path mode.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">No external scrubbing centers are used. Therefore, your will have the best possible latency.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">Usable for your Layer 2 and Layer 3 BGP IP-transit traffic.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=