d\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">Antennas up to 30 meters.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color:#FF692d\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">Different types of fastenings and security levels.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color:#FF692d\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">The Internet speed &mdash; up to 100 Gb/s.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color:#FF692d\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">The minimum cable length &mdash; approximately 20 meters.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color:#FF692d\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">Satellite dish is accessible 24х7х365.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color:#FF692d\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">The cost of installation and maintenance depends on several factors and is calculated after a detailed study of the request.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">For more information, please, contact our <a href=\"mailto:sales@hostkey.com\"><span style=\"color:#945AE0;\"><b>Sales department</b></span></a></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','section/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/87/promo_text_05_satellite.png'),(88,81,'/solutions/colocation','colocation',NULL,'Content_Page','Content_Section_About','no','yes','yes','yes',70,'Colocation','Colocation',NULL,'Colocation','Colocation','Colocation','<p>We won&rsquo;t accept your claim/complaint about violation of copyright and associated rights unless made in writing and delivered to us by registered mail.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our postal address: 19/2, Lva Tolstogo st., 119021, Moscow, Attn: Mir Telematiki Ltd.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The claim/complaint should include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Applicant name (first names and surname &mdash; for individuals, full trade name &mdash; for companies);</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Registered address &mdash; for companies, registered address and/or place of residence &mdash; for individuals (apartment /suite, street, city, region, republic/country and zip code), i.e. the address to which a reply to your claim/complaint should be sent to; and your e-mail address;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>State registration certificate data &mdash; for companies; identity document (passport or its equivalent) data &mdash; for individuals;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your claim/complaint should specify the grounds for its filing and all material facts. If any materials/documents/information etc. are available on any websites and that violates any copyright, your claim/complaint should necessarily indicate full references to specific page (pages) of the website on which the given information and materials are located.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also the claim should state that the applicant undertakes to indemnify for losses incurred by the Operator in case of unauthorized website ban, if afterwards the claim is proved to contain false information about violation of the applicant&#39;s copyright.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The claim should be accompanied by certified copies of documents proving the applicant&#39;s copyright.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All pages of such enclosed copies should be signed and stamped by the applicant company chief executive; or such enclosed copies should be certified by a notary public if the applicant is an individual. The claim/complaint made for and on behalf of a company should be signed and stamped by its chief executive or by any authorized representative acting under the power-of-attorney, the copy of which to be enclosed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The claim made for and on behalf of an individual applicant should be signed by the applicant itself; and the signature on the claim should be certified by a notary public.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All claims/complaints are being considered within 60 days. In case of claim satisfaction, infringing materials could be directly deleted with any technical means. The company will take all necessary measures and will notify the applicant about it by e-mail indicated in the claim. If a claim is not accepted for satisfaction or the remedy is not feasible, the company shall provide the applicant with the grounds for its refusal in writing by mail to the address indicated in the claim.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Any claims made by anonyms or delivered by e-mail or fax WILL NOT be accepted and considered.</p>','section/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/88/promo_text_04_collocation.png'),(89,81,'/solutions/russia','russia',NULL,'Content_Page','Content_Section_ServiceInRussia','no','yes','yes','yes',80,'Service in Russia','Service in Russia',NULL,'Service in Russia','Service in Russia','Service in Russia','<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\">We won&rsquo;t accept your claim/complaint about violation of copyright and associated rights unless made in writing and delivered to us by registered mail.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\">Our postal address: 19/2, Lva Tolstogo st., 119021, Moscow, Attn: Mir Telematiki Ltd.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\">The claim/complaint should include:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\">Applicant name (first names and surname &mdash; for individuals, full trade name &mdash; for companies);</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\">Registered address &mdash; for companies, registered address and/or place of residence &mdash; for individuals (apartment /suite, street, city, region, republic/country and zip code), i.e. the address to which a reply to your claim/complaint should be sent to; and your e-mail address;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\">State registration certificate data &mdash; for companies; identity document (passport or its equivalent) data &mdash; for individuals;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\">Your claim/complaint should specify the grounds for its filing and all material facts. If any materials/documents/information etc. are available on any websites and that violates any copyright, your claim/complaint should necessarily indicate full references to specific page (pages) of the website on which the given information and materials are located.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\">Also the claim should state that the applicant undertakes to indemnify for losses incurred by the Operator in case of unauthorized website ban, if afterwards the claim is proved to contain false information about violation of the applicant&#39;s copyright.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\">The claim should be accompanied by certified copies of documents proving the applicant&#39;s copyright.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\">All pages of such enclosed copies should be signed and stamped by the applicant company chief executive; or such enclosed copies should be certified by a notary public if the applicant is an individual. The claim/complaint made for and on behalf of a company should be signed and stamped by its chief executive or by any authorized representative acting under the power-of-attorney, the copy of which to be enclosed.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\">The claim made for and on behalf of an individual applicant should be signed by the applicant itself; and the signature on the claim should be certified by a notary public.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\">All claims/complaints are being considered within 60 days. In case of claim satisfaction, infringing materials could be directly deleted with any technical means. The company will take all necessary measures and will notify the applicant about it by e-mail indicated in the claim. If a claim is not accepted for satisfaction or the remedy is not feasible, the company shall provide the applicant with the grounds for its refusal in writing by mail to the address indicated in the claim.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\">Any claims made by anonyms or delivered by e-mail or fax WILL NOT be accepted and considered.</span></p>','section/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/89/promo_text_03.png'),(90,80,'/web/container','container','/cloud/vps',NULL,NULL,'no','yes','yes','yes',NULL,'Container VPS','Container VPS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(91,50,'/dedicated/vds','vds','/cloud/vds',NULL,NULL,'no','yes','yes','yes',20,'VDS','VDS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(92,12,'/admin/site/contentlittle','contentlittle',NULL,'Zero_Main','Content_ContentLittle_Grid','yes','yes','yes','yes',50,'Текстовые вставки','Текстовые вставки',NULL,'Текстовые вставки','Текстовые вставки','Текстовые вставки',NULL,NULL),(93,92,'/admin/site/contentlittle/edit','edit',NULL,'Zero_Main','Content_ContentLittle_Edit','yes','yes','no','yes',10,'Текстовые вставки изменение','Текстовые вставки изменение',NULL,'Текстовые вставки изменение','Текстовые вставки изменение','Текстовые вставки изменение',NULL,NULL),(94,12,'/admin/site/faq','faq',NULL,'Zero_Main','Content_Faq_Grid','yes','yes','yes','yes',60,'Faq','Faq',NULL,'Faq','Faq','Faq',NULL,NULL),(95,94,'/admin/site/faq/edit','edit',NULL,'Zero_Main','Content_Faq_Edit','yes','yes','no','yes',10,'Faq Изменение','Faq Изменение',NULL,'Faq Изменение','Faq Изменение','Faq Изменение',NULL,NULL),(96,76,'/about/network','network',NULL,'Content_Page','Content_Section_Page','no','yes','yes','yes',30,'Network','Network','About Network SOLUTIONS нггшщшщщ','Network','Network','Network','<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">HOSTKEY&rsquo;s network is connected to the largest carriers and traffic exchange points, which guarantees the availability of resources.</span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#FF692d;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\"><span style=\"font-size:26px\"><strong>Russia</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">HOSTKEY&nbsp;is connected to networks of such telecom operators as RETN, NETBYNET, etc. that have direct channels to CITY SYSTEMS, DATALINE and DATAPRO data centers. Networks of these operators are based on highly reliable telecommunication equipment and have multiple redundancy that provides network accessibility of server equipment.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">Connection to the network of the international operator RETN makes it possible to provide services with high level of accessibility not only in the Russian Federation:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">The network uses Internet Exchange nodes in Europe, USA and Asia, and it is constantly growing.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color: rgb(255, 105, 45);\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">It is capable of maintaining 100G channels, with a total of 7.2Tbit/s per fiber pair.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#FF692d;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\"><span style=\"font-size:26px\"><strong>The Netherlands</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">HOSTKEY has a reserved connection to Serverius network and RETN several traffic exchange points, in particular AMS-IX:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"color:#FF692d\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">Serverius network provides a mix of huge amount of peering and ip-transit providers: AMS-IX, DE-CIX, Gtt Tinet, Level3, DE-CIX, TATA communications, NL-IX, RETN and many other partial and full transit and private fiber peers.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"color:#FF692d\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(39, 46,56);\">Each peering or carrier is connected to multiple 10G ports and is part of the 300Gbps network that is running on our redundant 400Gbps transport backbone to multiple Amsterdam and Frankfurt data centers. Route preferences are not specified, so you always get the shortest routes to other networks.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicbookcondc;\">It allows us to provide our clients with multiple ports, thus ensuring a complete redundancy.</span></span></p>','section/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/100/96/_promo_news.jpg'),(97,76,'/about/datacenter','datacenter',NULL,'Content_Page','Content_Section_Page','no','yes','yes','yes',40,'DataCenter','DataCenter',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p><span style=\"font-family:franklingothicmedicondosc\"><span style=\"font-size:28px\"><strong>HOSTKEY&#39;S DATA CENTERS</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><span style=\"font-fa